# AWS Lambda Deployment Using Serverless Framework (Node.js)

This project demonstrates how to deploy a simple AWS Lambda function using the **Serverless Framework**.
It is designed for **beginners and freshers** to understand real-world DevOps deployment flow.

---

## ðŸ§  What You Will Learn

- What is AWS Lambda
- What is Serverless Framework
- How to deploy Lambda using CLI
- Infrastructure as Code (IaC) basics
- How AWS IAM & CloudFormation work together

---

## ðŸ›  Prerequisites

- AWS Account
- IAM User with AdministratorAccess
- Node.js installed
- Serverless Framework installed

---

## ðŸ”§ Install Serverless Framework

```bash
npm install -g serverless


Verify:

serverless -v

ðŸ” Configure AWS Credentials (One-Time)
serverless config credentials \
  --provider aws \
  --key YOUR_ACCESS_KEY \
  --secret YOUR_SECRET_KEY

ðŸ“ Project Structure
AWS-Nodejs-app/
 â”œâ”€â”€ handler.js        # Lambda function code
 â”œâ”€â”€ serverless.yml    # Infrastructure definition
 â””â”€â”€ README.md

ðŸ§¾ handler.js (Lambda Code)
module.exports.hello = async (event) => {
  return {
    statusCode: 200,
    body: JSON.stringify({
      message: "Hello from AWS Lambda ðŸš€"
    })
  };
};

ðŸ— serverless.yml (Infrastructure as Code)
service: AWS-Nodejs-app

provider:
  name: aws
  runtime: nodejs18.x
  region: us-east-1

functions:
  hello:
    handler: handler.hello

ðŸš€ Deploy to AWS
serverless deploy


Expected output:

Service deployed to stack AWS-Nodejs-app-dev
functions:
  hello: AWS-Nodejs-app-dev-hello

â–¶ï¸ Invoke Lambda Function
serverless invoke -f hello


Output:

{
  "statusCode": 200,
  "body": "Hello from AWS Lambda ðŸš€"
}

ðŸ§¹ Cleanup Resources (Important)
serverless remove


This deletes:

Lambda function

CloudFormation stack

Related IAM resources

